=Description=

"What do we mean by a manufacturing grid and how would it be used? A
working definition is “the harnessing of distributed manufacturing resources
to satisfy emerging business requirements.” In practice, this requires an
interconnected mesh of operations and services between businesses with
different customers, markets and organisational goals. This would enable
spare production or distribution capacity in one company to be available to
other organisations, maximising the efficiency of the whole network.
To make this work, an information structure is required that connects
those wanting to buy manufacturing services with a compatible set of
suppliers. The structure must also support contract placement, product
design, agreement on delivery schedules, transfer of data and quality
guarantees. While data is at the heart of the grid, it must also enable the
effi cient movement of physical goods."
(http://www.ifm.eng.cam.ac.uk/service/cmr/04cmrspring/ifmfocus.pdf)





